-- Dubai 2009 Unemployment Rate Drops 19% From Year Before, Gulf News Reports
-- Zainab Fattah
-- 2010-07-16T07:57:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/dubai-2009-unemployment-rate-drops-19-from-year-before-gulf-news-reports.html

          
          
             Dubaiâ€™s unemployment rate stood at
0.8 percent in 2009, a fall of 19 percent from the previous
year,  Gulf News  reported, citing Dubai Statistics Centre data.  
 A total of 11,152 people were unemployed last year out of
1.36 million of the economically active population, which makes
up 86.6 percent of the 1.57 million residents, the newspaper
reported. Among the jobless, 7,179 were expatriates and 3,973
were citizens, Gulf News said.  
 Employment laws in the United Arab Emirates require
dismissed workers to leave the country within 30 days following
the termination of their employment visas.  
